title: stronger types on should(foo).equal(bar)
body:
Hi. 

In typescript I think it's fair to assume that 
if two objects are tested to be equal, they should be of the same type.

I.e. it would be nice if `foo.should.equal(bar)` threw a compile-time error
if foo and bar where different types.

We can't really support this because shouldjs extends Object, 
except for the case of `should(foo).equal(bar)`,  but why not
support it in that case? 

Editors such as VS will also be able to offer increased intellisense auto complete
if we write `bar` as an anonymous object.

Cheers

title: [JointJS] Add missing methods from js, concretize generics on classes inheriting from BackboneJS, fix generics in classes dependent on JointJS (rappid)
body:
Essentially I added three things to the definitions:
- Methods on Graph, Paper, Cell and util which are present in the js source but not in the typings
- Added generics to some classes which inherit from Backbone
- Added type defintions for joint.shapes.devs.Model which is used in the official tutorials and is present in a separate file in the node package

Please see the commit messages for more details on each topic.

title: Changed type of "data" to { [key: string]: any; }
body: Changed the type of the data property on the IFieldGroup, ITypeOptions, IFormOptionsAPI, and IFieldConfigurationObject interfaces from "Object" to a hash of string to any. While Object was not incorrect, it made use without a cast a type error in all but the most trivial cases.
